<img class="aligncenter wp-image-1081433 lazyload" src="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/faaji-friday-2-guardian-life.jpeg" alt="" width="1280" height="800" srcset="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/faaji-friday-2-guardian-life.jpeg 640w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/faaji-friday-2-guardian-life-487x304.jpeg 487w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/faaji-friday-2-guardian-life-320x200.jpeg 320w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/faaji-friday-2-guardian-life-600x375.jpeg 600w" sizes="(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px" /> What better way to have your Friday this 20th of December than the Faji way. It is Faji Friday 2.0 with EmmaOhMyGod at the Shell Hall, Muson Center, Lagos. Unlike the conventional musical or comedy shows this season, guests can look forward to a family-friendly night of dancing, total enjoyment, and fun, with the OhEmGee band’s renditions of popular song covers, hymns, comedy, music-comedy, and live band music. The event will also feature guest appearances from artistes and comedians such as Alibaba, Kennyblaq, Ric Hassani, SLK, Bez Idakula, Helen Paul, Josh2funny and many more. The first episode happened last year and it was “awemazing”.  In three weeks, the event centre was totally filled up as people were eager to experience something different from the usual. This year promises to be different. This year’s edition started with pop sales at the Palms Malls Lekki with couples, parents, and children having a band playing for them. Also, with so many brands partnering for the event, ultimate enjoyment galore is guaranteed. Come out and have a “faajified” Friyayyy …